12. The office of a member of the Commission shall be vacated if—
(a) he dies;
(b) there has been proved against him, or he has been convicted
of, a charge in respect of—
(i) an offence involving fraud, dishonesty or moral
turpitude;
(ii) an offence under any law relating to corruption; or
Competition Commission
